      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues] Line 91: The new buffering path only works when `operationId \u003d\u003d 0`, but `sendAuthentication()` does not reset `operationId` before installing the next subscription. On a retry/reuse, `operationId` still contains the previous operation id while `addDevice()` is running, so an early callback for the new operation is not buffered and is discarded because it does not match the stale id. Reset the per-operation state before subscribing/calling `addDevice()`.\n```suggestion\n        codeProvided \u003d true\n        operationId \u003d 0\n        pendingAuthResults.removeAll()\n\n        authOperationDisposable.disposable \u003d self.accountService.authStateSubject\n```",
